    "text": "‚öôÔ∏è Technical SEO Basics: The Core of a Healthy Website\nTechnical SEO is the foundation that helps search engines properly crawl and understand your site. Without it, even great content struggles to rank.\n\nüîß Website Speed\n Fast-loading pages improve user experience and boost rankings.\nüì± Mobile-Friendly Design\n Google prioritizes sites that work smoothly on mobile. Responsive layouts and easy navigation are essential.\nüó∫Ô∏è XML Sitemap\n Acts as a roadmap, helping search engines find your important pages quickly.\nüö´ Robots.txt\n Tells search engines what to crawl and what to skip. A wrong setup can block key pages.\nüîÅ Fix Broken Links\n 404 errors and broken links hurt both users and crawl efficiency. Regular checks are important.\nüîê HTTPS Security\n Secure websites build trust and rank better than non-secure sites.\nüè∑Ô∏è Structured Data\n Schema markup helps search engines understand your content and can earn rich results.\nüìÇ Canonical Tags\n Prevents duplicate content by showing Google which page is the main version.\nüéÜ  Bottom Line:\n A strong technical setup makes your website faster, safer, and more search-friendly ‚Äî giving all your SEO efforts a solid base.\n\n#SEO #TechnicalSEO #DigitalMarketing #SearchEngineOptimization #ContentStrategy #MarketingInsights",
