    "text": "Standing still is now the most expensive strategy in search.\n\nIf you work in higher ed marketing, SEO can feel like trying to untangle all your Christmas lights in one sitting. Too many pages. Too many directions. Too many unknowns. So‚Ä¶ where do you even begin? üéÑ\n\nHere‚Äôs the good news no one says loud enough:\n\nYou don‚Äôt need to rebuild your entire website to stay competitive.\n\nSmall steps actually matter more than ever.\n\nWith the way search is evolving ‚Äî between SEO, AEO, GEO and all the AI discovery shifts ‚Äî performance drops off fast if you do nothing. But even a single update on a priority program page can make meaningful movement.\n\nTiny wins stack. Momentum compounds. Search rewards progress.\n\nSo if you feel stuck, or frozen, or like you don‚Äôt even know where to begin ‚Äî start smaller than you think you should.\n\nFix one H1.\n\nRewrite the intro on one core page so it actually speaks to a prospective student (not the catalog).\n\nSurface the RMI form so it‚Äôs one click away.\n\nEven as 2026 dawns on the horizon, small, regular updates will give you the foundation you need to stay afloat.\n\nRead our SEO expert's full recommendations in our blog:\nhttps://hubs.li/Q03T1ZCQ0\n\n\n#HigherEdMarketing #DigitalStrategy #GEO #AIsearch #InboundMarketing #AEO #GEO #searchoptimization #higheredSEO",
