    "authorHeadline": "Master of Business Administration",
    "title": "The Impact Of AI On Marketing And B2B Websites - B2B Marketing",
    "text": "Organic traffic dropped 30% across B2B companies. The solution isn't better SEO. It's something called generative engine optimization that most marketers haven't heard of.\n\nGEO focuses on optimizing for AI tools like ChatGPT and Perplexity. Not Google.\n\nB2B buyers now research using AI before they ever hit your website. Your content needs to feed these systems.\n\nBut here's what's really changing the game:\n\nüîç 80% of B2B companies plan AI integration by 2025\nüìà AI-powered personalization delivers 8x ROI\n‚ö° Fast-growing companies generate 40% more revenue from AI personalization\n\nThe bigger shift? Compliance is now driving infrastructure decisions.\n\nGDPR and data sovereignty rules are forcing hosting choices. Privacy isn't just legal anymore. It's strategic.\n\nMeanwhile, marketing and sales teams struggle with AI-powered lead scoring. The technology is there. The alignment isn't.\n\nBuyers self-research through AI tools. But they still need human reassurance at decision moments.\n\nThe winning approach treats AI as a teammate. Not a replacement.\n\nFocus on your digital foundations first. Then layer AI thoughtfully.\n\nDon't chase every new tool. Chase business results.\n\nWhat's your biggest AI challenge right now? SEO optimization or team alignment?\n\n#B2BMarketing #ArtificialIntelligence #DigitalStrategy\n\nùó¶ùóºùòÇùóøùó∞ùó≤Íûâ https://lnkd.in/gWf6Y8tu",
