    "authorName": "Faizat Hussein",
    "authorHeadline": "SEO & Brand Specialist | | On-Page, Technical & Content Strategy | Creator of Before The World Hits‚Ñ¢ | Recognized Branding Voice (Favikon Top 93)",
    "title": "",
    "text": "It‚Äôs been almost a year since I niched down to SEO management, and here are 5 things I‚Äôve learnt\n\n1. LLM Optimization is Inevitable\nStarting now, SEOs isn‚Äôt just optimizing for Google. It requires optimizing for AI models that read and summarize your content. \n\nBrands will compete not just for ranking but for representation in AI-generated answers. Understanding how AI interpret content will soon become a skill as essential as keyword research.\n\n2. SEO Rewards Consistency, Not Luck\nWhether it‚Äôs content, backlinks, or updates, consistency wins. The same principle applies to personal branding. \n\nShowing up regularly compounds your visibility. The difference between invisible and visible is usually six months of steady effort.\n\n3. On-page SEO is Only 10% of the Game\nOptimized titles, headings, and metadata are just the start. Real results come from depth, content clusters, internal linking, authority building, and technical precision. \n\nOn-page might SEO gets you indexed, but Strategic SEO brings result.\n\n4. SEO is Not Limited to Websites\nSearch is now multi-platform. Social media, YouTube, personal blogs, newsletters, they all have their own algorithms that reward visibility. \n\nTo be seen online, you can‚Äôt afford to think website-only. Every platform functions as a search engine now.\n\n5. Don‚Äôt Forget the Human\nYou can chase numbers, keywords, and click rates all day, but if your content doesn‚Äôt make sense to people, it won‚Äôt convert. \n\nThe goal of SEO isn‚Äôt traffic. It‚Äôs trust. And that starts with writing that connects to humans, not robots.",
