    "text": "Privacy laws now dictate where companies host their websites. Compliance became the top factor in hosting decisions. Marketing infrastructure choices follow legal requirements, not performance.\n\nThis shift reveals how AI is reshaping B2B marketing beyond the obvious.\n\nRecent roundtable data shows organic traffic dropped 30%. Teams are pivoting to generative engine optimization (GEO) instead of traditional SEO.\n\nBut here's what caught my attention:\n\n‚Ä¢ 80% of B2B companies plan AI integration by 2025\n‚Ä¢ AI-powered personalization delivers 8x ROI\n‚Ä¢ Traditional analytics miss AI-driven engagement patterns\n\nThe real challenge isn't the technology. It's organizational alignment.\n\nBuyers research independently using ChatGPT and similar tools. Yet they still need human reassurance at decision points.\n\nThis creates gaps between marketing and sales teams.\n\nAI works best when it augments strategy, not replaces it. Your website foundation and user journey remain critical.\n\nFocus on business objectives first. Then adopt AI thoughtfully.\n\nDon't chase every new tool. Start with pilot programs and governance reviews.\n\nThe companies winning treat AI as a teammate, not a magic solution.\n\nHow are you balancing AI innovation with compliance requirements in your marketing strategy?\n\n#AIMarketing #B2BMarketing #MarketingStrategy\n\nùó¶ùóºùòÇùóøùó∞ùó≤Íûâ https://lnkd.in/gt-_nYv8",
